title: Abbreviated conjunction and disjunction of three wff's

blocks.name: w3o
blocks.content: Extend wff definition to include three-way disjunction ('or').
blocks.origin: prop wff w3o(wff w0, wff w1, wff w2) { (w0 ∨ w1 ∨ w2) }

w3a
blocks.content: Extend wff definition to include three-way conjunction ('and').

df-3or
blocks.content: Define disjunction ('or') of three wff's. Definition *2.33 of [WhiteheadRussell] p. 105. This abbreviation reduces the number of parentheses and emphasizes that the order of bracketing is not important by virtue of the associative law ~ orass . (Contributed by NM, 8-Apr-1994.)

blocks.name: df-3an
blocks.content: Define conjunction ('and') of three wff's. Definition *4.34 of [WhiteheadRussell] p. 118. This abbreviation reduces the number of parentheses and emphasizes that the order of bracketing is not important by virtue of the associative law ~ anass . (Contributed by NM, 8-Apr-1994.)
